<title>SPAIN: Spain's Endesa to lay off 4,000 workers by 2001.</title>
<headline>Spain's Endesa to lay off 4,000 workers by 2001.</headline>
<dateline>MADRID 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Electricity company Endesa is to cut its workforce by 20 percent, offering early retirement to around 4,000 workers over four years, a company source said on Friday, confirming a press report.</p>
<p>&quot;The net impact will be of a reduction of 3,500 workers, because the firm is planning to hire new people in the meantime,&quot; the source said.</p>
<p>Currently Endesa's workforce totals 24,000.</p>
<p>The source added that the staff cut was an important part of a plan aimed to cut costs, announced recently.</p>
<p>At the beginning of May, Endesa chief executive Rafael Miranda said the firm intended to reduce overall expenditures by 310 billion pesetas before 2001.</p>
